<br />

<br />
For those rare few that we have captured the US government has taken the most extream methods they can use to pull what little information out of these people to try to protect this country. One of those was secret trials to insure that the type of criminal involved would serve US Military justice. It also insured that the final disposition and information collected of that prisoner would remain secret from both his allies and the public which at this time remains infiltrated and possible someparts of the military which may also be compromised. 
<br />

<br />
I dont agree with secret trials, but see the need for these special case people. On the other hand, beyond any use of this system, it should be illegal and Sec. of Homeland Security should step down / be forced to step down as soon as the Bush administration is over. His word is simply not good enough for the Homeland security act and due process must take place or criminal charges need to be found over what was done under his administration. 
<br />

